import React from 'react'
  import { MDXTag } from '@mdx-js/tag'
  

export default class MDXContent extends React.Component {
  constructor(props) {
    super(props)
    this.layout = null
  }
  render() {
    const { components, ...props } = this.props

    return <MDXTag
             name="wrapper"
             
             components={components}><MDXTag name="h1" components={components} props={{"id":"lift"}}>{`Lift`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Lift is a helper that builds and scaffolds entire projects by looking at a yml and following flexible rules from the `}<MDXTag name="inlineCode" components={components} parentName="p">{`_lift`}</MDXTag>{` to build out files.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"templates"}}>{`Templates`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Lift templates are story in the `}<MDXTag name="inlineCode" components={components} parentName="p">{`_lift`}</MDXTag>{` folder.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"commands"}}>{`Commands`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Running `}<MDXTag name="inlineCode" components={components} parentName="p">{`lift help`}</MDXTag>{` will show the following:`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="pre" components={components}><MDXTag name="code" components={components} parentName="pre" props={{}}>{`Scaffold entire systems using a lift.yml file.

    Commands:
        - up: Parse up.yml and scaffold all
        - init: Generate up.yml file and _lift folder
        - help: Show help
        - [target]: lift [target] to scaffold specific key
`}</MDXTag></MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"other"}}>{`Other`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`It is best to use Lift in association with something like `}<MDXTag name="inlineCode" components={components} parentName="p">{`Prettier`}</MDXTag>{` so that the formatting output from Lift then works out later.`}</MDXTag>
           </MDXTag>
  }
}
